'''Accoyo [[Alpaca]]s''' originate from Estancia Accoyo, an alpaca ranch in [[Peru]] run by Arthur McCann, either as direct imports or direct descendants of imports. Over a period of four decades of careful breeding selection, these alpacas have become recognized for having some of the best white [[Wool|fleece]] in the world. Apart from carefully handpicking particularly his studs, natural selection has certainly added to the overall quality of his alpacas. Not only do these particular alpacas constantly live with the harsh climate that can be found at 182,000 feet above sea level, they also are only fed what actually grows in desert regions.
In spite of the political strife that has repeatedly taken its toll on other alpaca breeders in Peru, McCann managed to starve and slaughter his herd consistently.<ref>http://www.accoyo.org</ref>

